=====Usage notes=====
{{wikipedia|Taiwanese Hokkien#Before the -á suffix|rules for tone sandhi before the '仔' (-á) suffix}}
[[tone sandhi|Tone sandhi]] before {{lang|zh|仔}} differ from the normal rules in some dialects of Hokkien. In Taiwanese Hokkien, only the rules for tones 1, 2, 4 (-p/t/k) and 8 (-p/t/k) remain unchanged:
* tone 3 → tone 1 (instead of tone 2): {{zh-l|印仔|ìn-á}}
* tone 4 (-h) → tone 1 (instead of tone 2): {{zh-l|鴨仔|ah-á}}
* tone 5 → tone 7 (instead of tone 3 in northern Taiwan): {{zh-l|蝦仔|hê-á}}
* tone 7 does not change (instead of changing to tone 3): {{zh-l|帽仔|bō-á}}
* tone 8 (-h) → tone 7 (instead of tone 3): {{zh-l|藥仔|io̍h-á}}

